HEADWORD: Scutter
<hw>Scut"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Scuttle</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety> <def>To run quickly; to
scurry; to scuttle.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark></p>

<p><q>A mangy little jackal . . . cocked up his ears and tail, and
<qex>scuttered</qex> across the shallows.</q>
<rj><qau>Kipling.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

